Reasoning: The paper deals with designing an autonomous agent for achieving optimal flexibility and efficiency in a multiagent system with no mechanisms for prior coordination. This involves game-theoretic modelling and planning procedures to find optimal actions. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with multiagent systems, which falls under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The use of Bayesian Nash equilibrium and optimal control also suggests relevance to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.RO (Robotics).
